news.title: China's Kaisa Group pressured by local government to repay wealth product investors
news.para: Kwok Ying Shing, chairman of the cash-strapped developer, has agreed to a request from the government of Shenzhen where the company is based, to provide by the end of January a proposal to repay investors in its wealth management products (WMPs), said one of the sources.

news.title: Mysuru civic body to start B khatas for illegal buildings
news.para: The MCC, which collects around Rs 160 crore in taxes, can hope to collect Rs 30 crore to Rs 60 crore more once these 50,000 properties are brought under taxation.

news.title: Indore civic body demolishes illegal portions of four buildings in Chikitsak Nagar
news.para: Continuing its crackdown against illegal constructions, Indore Municipal Corporation (IMC) on Friday demolished portions of four buildings in Chikitsak Nagar that were developed on permission of residential use but were operating as hotels there.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco includes 32 villages in Khopta New Town development
news.para: ​The new township involves 32 revenue villages encompassing Panvel and Uran talukas. This area includes 7 villages from Panvel tehsil of the Raigad district and 25 villages from the Uran tehsil.

news.title: Jaipur civic body to auction plots, shops to raise income
news.para: Around 72 shops and 10 kiosks near World Trade Park will be auctioned along with 14 residential plots in Gandhi Vihar scheme near the airport and 24 residential plots & two commercial plots in Gandhi Enclave Scheme at Sirsi Road.

news.title: Odisha CM disburses Rs 3,000 each to 31 lakh families for house repair
news.para: The state government will soon provide Rs 5,000 each to the 12.25 lakh households who have been denied a pucca house under the Pradham Mantri Aawas Yojana (Gramin), the chief minister said.

news.title: Mysuru civic body collects record Rs 133 crore in property tax
news.para: With one quarter still to go, the civic body hopes to add another Rs 50 crore in property taxes, registering an all-time high. Of the 1,83,949 properties in MCC limits, 1,58,593 are general properties and 25,379 are revenue properties categorised as commercial and super commercial.

news.title: BMC to construct 700 tenements for PAPs
news.para: Ramesh Pawar, deputy municipal commissioner (Improvements) said the BMC owns a 75,000 sq feet plot at Worli of which 15,000 sq feet is encroached upon by slums.

news.title: Eight illegal colonies razed in Farrukhnagar
news.para: During the drive, the team, in the presence of 100 policemen, cleared around 50 acres of land and demolished 60 structures, including eight under-construction houses and two offices of property dealers.

news.title: Bengaluru: 11,000 of 78,000 property tax defaulters to get immediate relief
news.para: For, according to the BBMP, a majority of the 11,000 property owners have paid “excess” taxes when compared to the state government decision to only add a simple interest of 12 percent per annum to their pending taxes.

news.title: Gurugram: More ground coverage likely to be allowed in plots to curb violations
news.para: With the increase in ground coverage, plot owners will be able to construct lifts, staircases and cutouts without compromising the floor area ratio (FAR), which in turn, officials believe, will help bring down violations and unauthorised construction in plotted areas.

news.title: Offices of Supertech and GSS Buildcon shut in Greater Noida over dues
news.para: While Supertech has to pay up Rs 123 crore to comply with the orders of the housing regulatory authority, GSS Buildcon has to pay around Rs 6.6 crore.

news.title: China: Shimao Group seeks ABS extensions; shares, bonds sell off
news.para: Shimao Group's unit Shanghai Shimao Construction has proposed extensions on maturities for two asset-backed securities (ABS) due this month totalling 1.17 billion yuan ($183.50 million), three sources with knowledge of the matter told Reuters.

news.title: Drop in income during covid hits Lucknow civic body property tax collection target
news.para: According to LMC officials, against the target of Rs 34 crore property tax collection set for the three-month period from September to November, the municipal corporation has only managed to collect around Rs 5 crore so far.

news.title: Ashok Piramal Group's Peninsula Land defaults on Rs 77.24-crore debt obligations
news.para: The company owes Rs 66.14 crore as principal to RBL Bank at a 12.5% interest rate, a principal amount of Rs 172 crore to the State Bank of India at 9.05% and Rs 18.63 crore to Axis Bank at a 9.75% interest rate as on December 30. All of these are secured loans, the company said in a regulatory filing.
